How to identify manipulative situations and people,
& how to deal with them.
Manipulation in any situation, resulting in control of your behaviour, thoughts and actions, is a sign of an unhealthy and unbalanced / one-sided relationship.
Healthy social influence is part of the give and take of constructive relationships. In psychological manipulation, one person is used for the benefit of another. The manipulator deliberately creates an imbalance of power, and exploits to serve their own agenda.
Do any of these sound familiar to you in any of your relationships?
Controlling other people‚Äôs perceptions of you
This might sound like: ‚ÄúThey only like you because I lie to them about you!‚Äù
This could include spreading misinformation about you to others, and / or emphasising to you that others‚Äô good opinion of you is entirely dependent on their representation of you, and that you have them to thank for your own success.
Isolation
This might sound like: "I don't like your parents, they are not good to you and I don't want you to see them‚Äù, or telling you which friends you‚Äôre allowed to see.
Financial control
This might sound like: "You spend too much on yourself" / "Dear, you know you can't be trusted with money. It's best that I'm in charge."
Manipulative people will use financial control methods to gain power and control in relationships.
Financial abuse is one of the most powerful ways to keep someone trapped in a relationship, and can take subtle or overt forms to limit access to assets and accessibility to family finances. This is intentional and is used to entrap you in the relationship.
Dependence
This might come out in the form of drastic statements about what the manipulator might do if you don‚Äôt do what they ask, or over-reactions, such as obsessively calling you if you don‚Äôt answer at first.
This could be a form of emotional blackmail and might appear in exaggerated, dramatic language that makes you feel as though the other person‚Äôs wellbeing is entirely your responsibility.
Using your beliefs to control you
This might sound like: ‚ÄúHow will I get to heaven if I have a child like you?!‚Äù / ‚ÄúYou have no respect and will never pray for me when I am gone.‚ÄùThis exploits your beliefs for the benefit of the manipulator,resulting in controlling you and your actions.
